# Managed by chezmoi (source: private_dot_ssh/private_config).
#
# Client-side agent + keychain handling, so EVERY ssh consumer benefits
# (git, cron, launchd, GUI clients, IDEs) — not just interactive login shells.
# The zlogin hook stays as a belt-and-suspenders eager loader + ssh-reagent
# socket reuse; this config makes key-loading work everywhere else too.
#
#   AddKeysToAgent  load the key into the agent on first use (lazy)
#   UseKeychain     read/store the passphrase from the macOS keychain
#   IgnoreUnknown   UseKeychain is macOS-only — ignore (don't error) on Linux
Host *
  IgnoreUnknown UseKeychain
  AddKeysToAgent yes
  UseKeychain yes
  IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
  IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_rsa
